  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nFolks want the ability to determine the encodedGasLimit for their transactions given a specific actualGasLimit.\r\n\r\nTerminology refresher:\r\n- `actualGasLimit` = amount of gas which must be provided to execute the transaction.\r\n- `encodedGasLimit` = `fee + actualGasLimit`\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nAdd a L2Geth endpoint `rollup_getEncodedGasLimit` which accepts:\r\n\r\n- Input:\r\n  - `transaction` following EIP155 where `gasLimit` is provided & equals `actualGasLimit`.\r\n- Output:\r\n  - `encodedGasLimit` - calculated using the formulas outlined in: https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/823\r\n",
